# Frontend Architecture (React + TypeScript + Tailwind)

## Layer Rules

| Layer | Responsibility | Forbidden |
|-------|----------------|-----------|
| `pages/` | Compose features; wire hooks | Direct `fetch`, business logic |
| `components/features/` | Domain UI; props in, events out | Import from `services/` |
| `hooks/` | Bind services; loading/error state | JSX return |
| `services/` | HTTP calls; type mapping | React imports, component state |
| `stores/` | Auth session, UI prefs only | Duplicate API list cache |

## Data Fetching

- Server state: **TanStack Query** in hooks — not Zustand.
- Client state: **Zustand** (`authStore`, `uiStore`) only.
- API types mirror `docs/api/` in `types/api/`.

## Components

- UI primitives (`components/ui/`) — stateless, no API awareness.
- One component per folder with `index.ts` barrel export.
- Pages stay thin — extract markup to feature components.

## Services

- All HTTP via `services/api/httpClient.ts` with auth interceptor.
- One service file per API area (`scanService.ts`, `dashboardService.ts`).
- Unwrap `{ success, data, meta }` envelope from API conventions.

## Auth

- Tokens in `sessionStorage` via `authStore` — never in component local state.
- Route guards: `AuthGuard`, `RoleGuard` in `routes/guards/`.

## Styling

- Tailwind only — design tokens in `tailwind.config.ts`.
- No inline styles except dynamic values.

## Tests (_when added_)

- Hook tests with mocked services.
- Component tests with React Testing Library — no real API calls.
